    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
      <p>This collection, 1825-1953, consists chiefly of
         correspondence in the 1850's from the Allen family to John J.
         Allen, Jr., while he was in Texas. There is also
         correspondence between the family and Henry C. Allen and
         Robert E. Allen while they were students at the University of
         Virginia. There is much valuable commentary on contemporary
         political and social themes, but the strength of this
         collection lies in the insight it lends to the study of a
         family unit in the 1850's.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement>
      <head>Arrangement</head>
      <p>The collection has been single foldered and arranged in
         chronological order.</p>
    </arrangement>
